description:
Analyze the social network graph in the 'demodb' database to find connections between users. Document the shortest bidirectional friendship paths from 'john.smith@example.com' to 'thomas.schafer@example.com' and 'elena.petrakis@example.com'. Determine if a path exists between 'john.smith@example.com' and 'yuki.tanaka@example.com', and identify all 'friends of friends' (exactly 2 hops away, excluding direct friends and himself) for 'john.smith@example.com'. Treat 'HasFriend' edges as bidirectional. Save the results to '/home/ga/shortest_path_results.json' using the following format:
{
  "path_to_schafer": {
    "hops": <number>,
    "path_emails": ["email1", "email2", ...]
  },
  "path_to_petrakis": {
    "hops": <number>,
    "path_emails": [...] 
  },
  "path_to_tanaka_exists": <boolean>,
  "friends_of_friends": ["emailA", "emailB", ...]
}
